Prerequisites

Formulas

  • Indexed blood volume1: \(BV_i = \frac{70}{\sqrt{\frac{BMI}{22}}}\)2
  • Estimated blood volume: \(BV_e = BV_i \cdot Weight\)3
  • Blood loss ratio: \(BL_r = \frac{BV_e}{BL_a}\)4
  • Standardization method for age and bmi5: \(M_i = \frac{0.6745(x_i - \tilde(x))}{2 \cdot MAD}\)6

  1. Lemmens, H. J. M., Bernstein, D. P., & Brodsky, J. B. (2006). Estimating blood volume in obese and morbidly obese patients. Obesity Surgery, 16(6), 773776. https://doi.org/10.1381/096089206777346673
